div.ab:
O still Thyself, and let men go to their works! Thou art a son of the poor, learn
               from Thyself that all the poor had to leave their work to come. Thou who lovest men,
               hast bound men together by Thy gladsomeness.

Because the hidden fire of the lust of the body ruled not in him, to him the fire
               from on high was obedient. And since he subdued on the earth the lust of the flesh,
               he went up thither where holiness dwells and is at peace.
